definition.value: An oxopurine in which the purine ring is substituted by oxo groups at positions 2 and 6 and N-9 is protonated.
A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having adenine as the nucleobase.

A glycosylglucose disaccharide, found most notably in milk, that consists of D-galactose and D-glucose fragments bonded through a beta-1->4 glycosidic linkage. The glucose fragment can be in either the alpha- or beta-pyranose form, whereas the galactose fragment can only have the beta-pyranose form.
A D-glucopyranose 6-phosphate in which the anomeric centre has beta-configuration.

A fluoroindole that is 1H-indole substituted by phenyl, 4-{[(2S)-5-carbamimidamido-1-methoxy-1-oxopentan-2-yl]amino}-4-oxobutyl, fluoro and fluoro groups at positions 2, 3, 5 and 7, respectively. It is a selective nonpeptidic agonist of the somatostatin subtype-4 (SST4) receptor with Ki of 0.7 nM.

A benzoindole that is 1H-benzo[g]indole substituted by naphthalen-2-yl and 2-({(2R)-6-amino-1-[(2S)-2-aminopropoxy]-1-oxohexan-2-yl}amino)-2-oxoethyl groups at positions 2 and 3, respectively. It is a selective nonpeptidic agonist of the somatostatin subtype-5 (SST5) receptor with Ki of 0.4 nM.
An N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of beta-D-galactosyl-1,3-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,6)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine
An N-methylglycine that is glycine carrying two N-methyl substituents.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl residue attached to the galactose residue of N-acetyllactosamine via an alpha-(2->6)-linkage.
